---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Tree Removal Woy Woy | Peninsula Arborist & Storm Work"
  description="Tree services on the Woy Woy peninsula — removal, lopping & pruning, stump grinding, RFS 10/50 clearing and 24/7 storm work by qualified arborists. Angophora-heavy bushfire-prone blocks. Free quote."
  canonical="https://centralcoasttreeservice.com.au/woy-woy/">
  <Fragment slot="head">
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Woy Woy &middot; Umina Beach &middot; Ettalong &middot; Blackwall</span>
      <h1>Tree services on the <span class="accent">Woy Woy</span> peninsula.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        The Woy Woy peninsula is angophora country &mdash; Sydney red gums on sandy,
        bushfire-prone blocks hemmed by Brisbane Water and the Bouddi escarpment.
        Removal, AS 4373 pruning, stump grinding, RFS 10/50 hazard-reduction and
        24/7 storm work by qualified arborists. Free written quote on site.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Tree work on the peninsula</span>
      <h2>What we do around Woy Woy.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Angophora-heavy blocks &mdash; managed by people who know the species.</h3>
        <p>
          The Woy Woy peninsula &mdash; Woy Woy, Umina Beach, Ettalong, Blackwall and
          Booker Bay &mdash; is heavy with <strong>Sydney red gum (Angophora
          costata)</strong> on sandy, free-draining soil. Angophora is a beautiful,
          gnarled, salmon-barked tree and a defining feature of the peninsula, but
          it's also the eucalypt most prone to <strong>sudden summer limb drop</strong>,
          shedding large limbs in still, hot weather without warning. Managing
          angophora well is about correct <a href="/services/tree-lopping/">deadwooding
          and crown reduction to AS 4373</a> &mdash; never topping, which only makes the
          tree more dangerous &mdash; and knowing which limbs over a house genuinely need
          to come off.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">RFS 10/50 bushfire clearing.</h3>
        <p>
          Large parts of the peninsula sit on <strong>RFS-mapped bushfire-prone
          land</strong>, hemmed by bushland and the Bouddi National Park escarpment.
          Where your property is inside the <strong>10/50 Vegetation Clearing
          Entitlement Area</strong> (check your address on the NSW Rural Fire Service
          online tool), the code lets you clear trees within 10m of a home and
          underlying shrubs within 50m, without a separate Council approval, to reduce
          fuel near the house. We confirm eligibility against the RFS tool before
          relying on it, then create a proper defendable space &mdash; see
          <a href="/services/land-clearing/">land clearing &amp; hazard-reduction</a>.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Storm work &mdash; the peninsula cops it.</h3>
        <p>
          Sitting low and exposed between Brisbane Water and the ocean, the peninsula
          takes the full force of <strong>East Coast Lows</strong>, and angophora
          limb-drop spikes in big blows. We run <a href="/services/emergency-tree-removal/">24/7
          emergency and storm tree removal</a> across Woy Woy, Umina and Ettalong &mdash;
          limbs on roofs, trees across driveways, leaners on fences &mdash; making the
          site safe first and planning the full removal after. For dead and dangerous
          trees generally, see <a href="/services/tree-removal/">tree removal</a>.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Woy Woy jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Deadwooding a large angophora prone to summer limb drop over an Umina Beach roof</li>
          <li>RFS 10/50 hazard-reduction clearing around a bushfire-prone Blackwall block</li>
          <li>Sectional removal of a leaning, salt-stressed gum on a sandy Ettalong lot</li>
          <li>Emergency make-safe on a storm-felled limb across a Woy Woy carport</li>
          <li>Stump grinding after removal so the peninsula garden can be replanted</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/gosford/">Gosford</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/terrigal/">Terrigal</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/wyong/">Wyong</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/erina/">Erina</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/central-coast-region/">All Central Coast Region</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Woy Woy tree quote.</h2>
        <p>Angophora specialists. RFS 10/50 hazard-reduction. 24/7 peninsula storm response.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
